main event: A civilian reported seeing a pale red, cloud-like object in the sky over Hibbing, Minnesota on September 13, 1966.
interesting points: The object was witnessed at the Eveleth Weather Bureau.
Shortly after the sighting, a cloud release occurred at Port Churchill.
The sighting lasted for about 4 minutes.
The observed object was described as a 'pale red cloud type object'.
There were multiple rocket launches and cloud releases in the area around the time of the sighting.
result: identified as a cloud release from a Nike-Apache rocket launch
